        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 11:08PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 1108 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Leatherwood, or near Axton, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Martinsville...
Callands...
Sydnorsville...
Axton...
Snow Creek...
Leatherwood...
and Chatmoss.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
